      "id": "9e66cbd13eada499",
      "text": "> **Abstract**. Underlying [[Croquet]] is an object-oriented semantics based on active objects that have the capability of [[Temporal Reflection]]. That is, each object is aware and in direct control of its behavior in time. Croquet also directly supports [[Replication of Computation]], **allowing computation to be moved close to the point of interaction on demand**, while maintaining a consistent view of behaviors that can scale to include thousands of nodes. In the talk, we'll highlight the main concepts of **TeaTime**, which provides that semantic model, and also talk about some of the interesting implementation issues involved in realizing the TeaTime semantics.\n"
